<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-09T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-09T15:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113 Airplanes/103: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-09T16:00:00-04:00">May 9, 1935—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>32. Your 96, May 7, 3 p.m. The Department desires that you inform Beall
                            that as the proposed inquiry relates to the question of bringing about
                            notification to the Department that the Chinese Government desires that
                            export of the airplanes from the United States be authorized, the
                            Legation is not in position to interpose in a matter where the
                            initiative and responsibility lie with the Chinese Government and the
                            interested American firm.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>